With a beer or two, you can run up quite the check very quickly.  Overall though, definitely a great meal.

I was excited to see a new place in the neighborhood so I decided to take my father who was visiting from Michigan. Note to self: try a new restaurant first before taking others. This place is horrible. I knew the menu was limited before we went in so I knew what type of food to expect. I just didn't expect such horrible service and bees flying all over the restaurant. The interior was decent - I can understand how people find the TVs in the booths great for watching sports. Just don't order any food. We went with the $10 taco special (2 tacos, 2 salsas, 2 churros)...and sadly, the ancho salsa was the best item we consumed. The chips were oily, the lettuce was brown, and my Dad's chicken taco was hard as a rock. My brisket taco actually wasn't that bad and loaded with meat, but not enough to warrant a rating greater than 1 star. We actually never received the churros...and did not want to make a fuss since the service was overdue as it was and we did not want to get stung.  I was not expecting a Big Star or Antique Taco experience, but I certainly was expecting more than Taco Bell Cantina.

Pretty good Tex-Mex taco joint, considering Chicago has almost nothing of that sort anywhere, but it's not Torchy's. Definitely a great deal on $2 Taco Tuesdays, but otherwise they are somewhat pricy for their size, as I was still feeling hungry after 3. The tacos aren't bad, but with the style they're going for they simply aren't on par with Torchy's or the dozens of Tex Mex Staples in Austin which Chicago unfortunately does not have yet. I feel that their sauces or lack thereof are holding them back, along with minimal toppings, though the salsas are quite good. Fried meats are excellently done and bursting with flavor-- they simply need a wider variety of more unique sauces and toppings to complement them and bring everything together.

My goto $2 Taco Place was Closed, So I stopped in The Old Plank and I think they just won me over. I had a variety of Tacos as the list of different tacos was very diverse. I have to say the Fried Chicken Taco and Fish Taco were two of my Favorites. See you next Tuesday!

The Old Plank has potential, and I may try it again, but I must say I was disappointed the first time.  I had the brisket sandwich, and while the Texas Toast it was served on was good, some of the brisket itself was dry as a bone. We're talking not that far off from jerky. Some of it was decently moist, but the dry stuff was pretty awful. The BBQ sauce they used was pretty good and made the dry parts of the brisket edible, but man, just don't serve brisket if it's dry! Nobody looking for brisket wants that...  The service was decent though and if I just caught them on an off day, I'd be thrilled to try the brisket again if it's not normally dry.... So we might be back but I'm not entirely sure yet.

It is very aesthetically pleasing, very beautiful and large location! However, I did feel like it was a bit expensive. A mimosa is $9! The margarita was $10 and it was in a small cup rather than a margarita glass. I had the brisket taco and it was good! It was small for $4. The chips were too salty, at least for my taste but the tomatillo salsa was good!

Good place to go if you’re looking for somewhere to get drinks with friends and sit outside. - You can tell that the service is still figuring out logistics. It took 20 minutes after we were seated to get an order placed. However once we got our order done it took not even 10 minutes before we got our food. I think they’re still just working out the kinks as any new restaurant would. - The food we ordered was good. The cuisine is sort of a bbq and taco vibe. A rather limited menu compared to the other restaurants around it. The pictures added to this review are of the pulled pork sandwich and the brisket sandwich. Of which the pulled pork was significantly better. The brisket was far too smoky. Haven’t tried their tacos yet but I think those will be my next order when I go!

I posted this on my wife’s phone because I couldn’t log onto google tracking software.  Jay F Ramirez

Awesome spot to watch sports and enjoy a nice night, they even had the back door open so it was nice and breezy. Can’t wait to go back for brunch!
